	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>East India Chambers&#44; Leadenhall St.</placeName></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>London</placeName>&#44; <date>3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> July 1862</date></p>
				<p rend="align(center)"><add>Hebrew</add></p>
				<p rend="align(center)">JEWISH ASSOCIATION FOR THE DIFFUSION</p>
				<p rend="align(center)">OF RELIGIOUS KNOWLEDGE.</p>
				<p>Rev Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Will you be so kind as to inform<lb/> me at what price per hundred you<lb/> would be willing to supply your<lb/> translation of the Bible to the above<lb/> association.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I trust you will name the<lb/> lowest possible cost&#44; as the Association<lb/> require the Bibles for gratuitous distribution<lb/> among the poor.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">If it be not too much<lb/> trouble&#44; I should feel obliged by your<lb/> furnishing two separate estimates&#44;<lb/> one for the Bible bound&#44; complete&#44; as<lb/> supplied by your agent in <placeName>London</placeName>&#44;k<lb/> and the other for the Bible in reams&#44;<lb/> un&#45;bound.</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Awaiting your reply&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">I have the honor to be&#44; Rev Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">Your obedt Servt.</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">N. S. Joseph</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">Hon Secry</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
